      • form

        public static void form(ChainedHttpConfig config,
                        ToServer ts)

        Standard encoder for requests with content type 'application/x-www-form-urlencoded'. Accepts String and Map types. If the body is a String type the method assumes it is properly url encoded and is passed to the ToServer parameter as is. If the body is a Map type then the output is generated by the Form class.

        Parameters:
        config - Fully configured chained request
        ts - Formatted http body is passed to the ToServer argument

      • xml

        public static void xml(ChainedHttpConfig config,
                       ToServer ts)

        Standard encoder for requests with an xml body. <p> Accepts String and Closure types. If the body is a String type the method passes the body to the ToServer parameter as is. If the body is a Closure then the closure is converted to xml using Groovy’s StreamingMarkupBuilder.

        Parameters:
        config - Fully configured chained request
        ts - Formatted http body is passed to the ToServer argument

      • json

        public static void json(ChainedHttpConfig config,
                        ToServer ts)

        Standard encoder for requests with a json body. <p> Accepts String, GString and Closure types. If the body is a String type the method passes the body to the ToServer parameter as is. If the body is a Closure then the closure is converted to json using Groovy’s JsonBuilder.

        Parameters:
        config - Fully configured chained request
        ts - Formatted http body is passed to the ToServer argument
